5 ms is a safe assumption for tactile dome switches. Long-throw lever switches can bounce 20+ ms.

Non-blocking debounce in C:

```cpp
static uint32_t lastChange = 0;
static int lastStable = HIGH;
static int candidate = HIGH;
const uint32_t DEBOUNCE_MS = 5;

void loop() {
  int now = digitalRead(BUTTON_PIN);
  if (now != candidate) {
    candidate = now;
    lastChange = millis();
  }
  if (now != lastStable && (millis() - lastChange) >= DEBOUNCE_MS) {
    lastStable = now;
    onButton(lastStable);
  }
}
```

Same pattern in JS, replace millis() with Date.now() and run inside a subscribe loop.
